    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset contains 13 observations of four-dimensional financial data: three quantitative variables (valuation, revenue, profit/loss) and one nominal variable (company name). Original data from TechCrunch demonstrates strong outliers like Lyft's negative $911M profit and Zoom's outlier status as the only profitable IPO. Values show right-skewed distributions with valuation range $1.4B-$18.6B (\u03bc=$6.9B, \u03c3=$5.4B) and revenue range $0.088B-$2.16B. The bubble chart maximizes data-ink ratio by encoding three metrics in position/size while maintaining readability through Cairo's magnitude perception principles. Color differentiation (red=loss/green=profit) creates immediate categorical recognition. Proportional bubble areas (z-values range: -$0.911B to +$0.195B) use Stevens' power law for accurate magnitude estimation. Tooltip formatting follows D3-style financial annotations ($XB) for rapid quantitative parsing."
